  "prompt": "Where can I get audiobooks for free in English?",
  "response": "There are several platforms where you can access audiobooks in English for free:\n\n1. **LibriVox**: A volunteer-driven platform offering free audiobooks of public domain works. You can find classics and other works that are no longer under copyright.\n\n2. **Project Gutenberg**: Known primarily for its ebooks, Project Gutenberg also offers a selection of free audiobooks, especially for classic literature.\n\n3. **OverDrive/Libby**: Many public libraries offer free access to audiobooks through OverDrive or its app, Libby. You just need a library card to borrow audiobooks digitally.\n\n4. **Lit2Go**: A free online collection of stories and poems in audiobook format, it also provides useful background information for each work.\n\n5. **AudiobookSYNC**: A summer program primarily targeting teens, it offers free audiobook downloads of young adult titles, including both modern and classic literature.\n\n6. **YouTube**: While not an official audiobook provider, you can find many audiobooks uploaded by users. Be sure the uploads are legitimate and not infringing on copyrights.\n\n7. **Spotify**: Some audiobooks, particularly classics and public domain works, are available on Spotify. You can listen for free with ads or subscribe for ad-free listening.\n\n8. **Open Culture**: This site offers a curated list of free audiobooks, particularly classics and other works in the public domain, available from various sources on the web.\n\nWhen using these services, especially those that offer public domain works, it's important to check the copyright status and ensure that you're accessing legitimately free content.",
